All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
CargoSpace
Represents a three-dimensional cargo space in the context of a knapsack problem.
Cell
Represents a cell in the sparse matrix used by the Dancing Links algorithm.
Chromosome
Chromosome represents a potential solution to the knapsack problem in the context of a genetic algorithm.
DancingLinks
Implements the Dancing Links algorithm for solving exact cover problems, specifically applied to the context of a knapsack problem.
DLSearch
DLSearch orchestrates the search process using the Dancing Links algorithm for the knapsack problem.
EquilibriumAndDistribution
EquilibriumAndDistribution handles the placement of parcels in a CargoSpace and calculates metrics like the center of mass and distribution of parcels within the cargo space.
Experiment
 
FileUtil
Provides utility functions for file operations, such as writing text to a file.
GeneticKnapsackSolver
GeneticKnapsackSolver implements a genetic algorithm to solve the knapsack problem.
GreedyKnapsackSolver
GreedyKnapsackSolver implements a greedy algorithm to solve the knapsack problem.
Header
Represents a header cell in the sparse matrix used by the Dancing Links algorithm.
KnapsackSolverApp
 
Parcel
Represents a parcel with specific characteristics such as value, type, shape, and ID.
ParcelBuilder
A class responsible for generating and managing the database of parcel shapes.
ParcelDatabase
 
ParcelInfo
Represents detailed information about a parcel in the context of the knapsack problem.
ParcelPlacement
Represents the placement of a parcel within a cargo space, extending the Parcel class to include position and color information for visualization purposes.
ShapesAndRotations
ShapesAndRotations manages the predefined shapes and rotations of parcels used in the knapsack problem.
UI
UI provides a graphical user interface to visualize the knapsack problem solutions.
